.TH "kernel_sendpage" 9 "kernel_sendpage" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
kernel_sendpage \- send a &page through a socket (kernel space)
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" kernel_sendpage
.BI "(struct socket *sock "  ","
.BI "struct page *page "  ","
.BI "int offset "  ","
.BI "size_t size "  ","
.BI "int flags "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "sock" 12
socket
.IP "page" 12
page
.IP "offset" 12
page offset
.IP "size" 12
total size in bytes
.IP "flags" 12
flags (MSG_DONTWAIT, ...)

Returns the total amount sent in bytes or an error.
